quran[18]{c,v,t,f}:
  26,148,"And green crops (fields) and date-palms with soft spadix."
  26,149,""
  26,150,""
  29,61,"And if you were to ask them: "
  29,62,"Allâh enlarges the provision for whom He wills of His slaves, and straitens it for whom (He wills). Verily, Allâh is the All-Knower of everything."
  29,63,"And if you were to ask them: "
  30,40,"Allâh is He Who created you, then provided food for you, then will cause you to die, then (again) He will give you life (on the Day of Resurrection). Is there any of your (so-called) partners (of Allâh) that do anything of that? Glory be to Him! And Exalted be He above all that (evil) they associate (with Him)."
  30,41,"Evil (sins and disobedience to Allâh) has appeared on land and sea because of what the hands of men have earned (by oppression and evil deeds), that He (Allâh) may make them taste a part of that which they have done, in order that they may return (by repenting to Allâh, and begging His Pardon)."
  30,42,"Say (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم): "
  31,25,"And if you (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) ask them: "
  31,26,"To Allâh belongs whatsoever is in the heavens and the earth. Verily, Allâh, He is Al-Ghanî (Rich, Free of all needs), Worthy of all praise."
  31,27,"And if all the trees on the earth were pens and the sea (were ink wherewith to write), with seven seas behind it to add to its (supply), yet the Words of Allâh would not be exhausted. Verily, Allâh is All-Mighty, All-Wise."
  32,10,"And they say: "
  32,11,"Say: "
  32,12,"And if you only could see when the Mujrimûn (criminals, disbelievers, polytheists, sinners) shall hang their heads before their Lord (saying): "
  33,1,"O Prophet (Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم)! Keep your duty to Allâh, and obey not the disbelievers and the hypocrites (i.e., do not follow their advice). Verily, Allâh is Ever All-Knower, All-Wise."
  33,2,"And follow that which is revealed to you from your Lord. Verily, Allâh is Well-Acquainted with what you do."
  33,3,"And put your trust in Allâh, and Sufficient is Allâh as a Wakîl (Trustee, or Disposer of affairs)."